<TITLE> Chapainawabganj court jails former BNP lawmaker </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chapainawabganj, July 23 (bdnews24.com)  A Chapainawabganj court Monday sentenced former BNP lawmaker Prof Shahjahan Mia and two others to five-year rigorous imprisonment in an extortion case. The court also fined them Tk 10,000 each. They have to serve out six more months in prison for failure to pay the fine. Prof Shahjahan Mia, who was elected MP from Chapainawabganj-1 constituency, is the president of BNP's Chapainawabganj unit. District and sessions judge Hrishikesh Saha handed down the verdict. Two other convicts are Shibganj Municipality BNP chief Shafiqul Islam and BNP worker Ainal Haque. According to case details, the convicts extorted Tk 60,000 from Panaullah, who filed the case. He also alleged a death threat by the convicts. After the verdict was delivered, Shahjahan pleaded innocent to the case and said he would appeal to the High Court against the verdict. Panaullah, a resident of Jalmachhmari Mahalla of Shibganj Municipality, filed the case on April 23 with Shibganj Police Station. bdnews2
